files

Class PlayerInformationFileInterpreter

  • java.lang.Object
    • files.PlayerInformationFileInterpreter

  • public class PlayerInformationFileInterpreter
extends java.lang.Object
    Utility class which creates a reader and interpreter to read and then interpret the data from a file whose filename is passed via the constructor. This class calls methods from the 'GeneralFileReader' to carry out the reading of the file into a string array. Once the data is in the string array, this class will interpret the data from the string array based on the assumption that the read file follows the specified format for a "Player Information File".

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      PlayerInformationFileInterpreter(java.lang.String theFileName)
      At instantiation this immediately creates and executes, in sequence, both a reader and interpreter which will immediately read the file specified by the filename at instantiation, store the data in a string array, interpret the stored data based on the format of specified for "Player Information Files", and, upon the completion of instantiation, allow access to the interpreted data though several getter methods.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.String getHashAlgo()
      Returns a string, as imported from the input file, with the name of the algorithm used to generate the hash of the file data which was included with the file itself.
      java.lang.String getImportedHash()
      Returns a string, as imported from the input file, which represents the value of the hash that was included with the file.
      java.lang.String getPubKeyAlgo()
      Returns a string, as imported from the input file, with the name of the algorithm used to generate the public key for the player represented by the input file.
      java.lang.String getPubKeyFileName()
      Returns a string, as imported from the input file, with the name of the key file holding the public key of the player represented by the input file.
      java.lang.String getPvtKeyAlgo()
      Returns a string, as imported from the input file, with the name of the algorithm used to generate the private key for the player represented by the input file.
      java.lang.String getPvtKeyFileName()
      Returns a string, as imported from the input file, with the name of the key file holding the private key of the player represented by the input file.
      java.math.BigInteger getUID()
      Returns the value of the UID imported from the input file.
